data.enText: an area of low land that is always soft and wet because there is nowhere for the water to flow away to
Cows were grazing on the marshes.

tr: low-lying wet land with grassy vegetation
usually is a transition zone between land and water

value.def: A marsh is a wet, muddy area of land.

trans: 盐沼(在海岸附近，常遭咸水淹灌)
